  "response": "Money laundering is a serious financial crime with comprehensive legal frameworks designed to prevent, detect, and prosecute such activities. Here's an overview of the key legal aspects:\n\n1. International Legal Framework\n- UN Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) Recommendations\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. Key Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act\n- Counter-Terrorism Financing Laws\n- Proceeds of Crime legislation\n\n3. Primary Legal Requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Record-keeping requirements\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n\n4. Regulatory Bodies\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Central banks\n- Securities regulators\n- Law enforcement agencies\n\n5. Penalties\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Significant financial penalties\n- Asset seizure\n- Potential imprisonment\n\n6. Compliance Mechanisms\n- Risk-based approaches\n- Regular audits\n- Staff training\n- Internal control systems\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent criminal financial activities and maintain financial system integrity.",
